### Chat Service API Tests
### Use with VS Code REST Client or JetBrains HTTP Client

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080
@buyerId = 22222222-2222-2222-2222-222222222222
@runnerId = 33333333-3333-3333-3333-333333333333
@orderId = 11111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111111

### Variables to set after creating a chat room
@chatRoomId = {{createChatRoom.response.body.chat_room_id}}


### ===================
### Health Check
### ===================

### Health check
GET {{baseUrl}}/health


### ===================
### Chat Rooms
### ===================

### Create a new chat room
# @name createChatRoom
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/chat/rooms
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "order_id": "{{orderId}}",
  "buyer_id": "{{buyerId}}",
  "runner_id": "{{runnerId}}"
}

### Get chat rooms for buyer
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/chat/rooms/{{buyerId}}

### Get chat rooms for buyer with pagination
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/chat/rooms/{{buyerId}}?limit=10

### Get chat rooms for runner
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/chat/rooms/{{runnerId}}

### Close a chat room
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/chat/rooms/{{chatRoomId}}/close


### ===================
### Messages
### ===================

### Get messages for a chat room
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/chat/rooms/{{chatRoomId}}/messages

### Get messages with limit
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/chat/rooms/{{chatRoomId}}/messages?limit=10

### Get messages with pagination
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/chat/rooms/{{chatRoomId}}/messages?limit=10&page_state=<base64_token>


### ===================
### WebSocket Testing
### ===================
### Note: HTTP clients cannot test WebSocket connections directly.
### Use one of these methods to test WebSocket functionality:

### Method 1: wscat (npm install -g wscat)
### wscat -c "ws://localhost:8080/ws/{{chatRoomId}}?sender_id={{buyerId}}"

### Method 2: websocat (https://github.com/vi/websocat)
### websocat ws://localhost:8080/ws/{{chatRoomId}}?sender_id={{buyerId}}

### Method 3: Browser DevTools Console
### const ws = new WebSocket("ws://localhost:8080/ws/<chatRoomId>?sender_id=<senderId>");
### ws.onmessage = (e) => console.log(JSON.parse(e.data));
### ws.send(JSON.stringify({action: "sendMessage", chat_room_id: "<chatRoomId>", content: "Hello!"}));

### WebSocket Message Format:
### Send: {"action": "sendMessage", "chat_room_id": "<uuid>", "content": "Hello!"}
### Receive: {"action": "receiveMessage", "message_id": "<uuid>", "sender_id": "<uuid>", "content": "Hello!", "sent_at": "2024-01-15T10:30:00Z"}
